    // Section 7: floating poing bug guard
    // ==========================================================
    /*
    Why == is unreliable for floating point comparison:
    Computers cannot store fractional decimal numbers perfectly because they use binary memory slots.
    This limitation causes tiny fractions of a decimal to get shopped off during calculations.
    Due to the hidden mismatches, using == will eventually produce wrong numbers and misscalculations.

    What you should use instead:
    I prefer to use epsilon comparion which is also known as tolerance band technique.
    Epsilon subtracts 2 decimal variables to find the raw difference bewtween them.
    Then it checks if that isolated difference is smaller then the threshold variable.

    The specific espilon value I chose and why:
    I chose the value of 0.001 for the billing system.
    Its a tenth of a penny which is less then any cent that exists.
    It safely stops computer rounding bus without changing the number itself.
    */

